Safety Tips

Things you need to know!

Stay Informed: Keep yourself updated about the latest trends and tactics used by perpetrators to distribute CSAM.

Report Promptly: If you come across CSAM, report it immediately to the appropriate authorities or online platforms for swift action.

Secure Devices: Maintain strong security measures on your devices, including passwords, firewalls, and antivirus, to prevent unauthorized access to CSAM.

Educate Others: Spread awareness among friends, family, and community members about the dangers of CSAM and how to identify and report it.

Secure Devices: Maintain strong security measures on your devices, including passwords, firewalls, and antivirus software, to prevent unauthorized access to CSAM.

Support Victims: Offer support and resources to victims of CSAM, guiding them towards professional assistance and legal aid if needed.
